Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim @green beans{6%oz} if necessary. Thinly slice @chili pepper{1}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{5%tsp} in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add half the ginger and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil and a big pinch of salt and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken for pork.

In a small #bowl, combine @apricot jam{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{1} and 1/4 cup water.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add remaining ginger and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in jam mixture and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

> Use pan used for chicken.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice and green beans between plates. Top rice with chicken and drizzle with sauce. Garnish with chili to taste and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.